“主要是肉眼可见的一些改变，大体观察报告。
"Mainly visible to the naked eye are some of the changes reported in general observations.
”刘良对新京报记者说。
"Liu Liang told the Beijing News.
全文940字，阅读约需2分钟新京报记者 逯仲胜 王昱倩校对 王心华中科技大学同济医学院法医系教授刘良团队，已获得9例新型冠状病毒肺炎逝者的病理样本。
The full text of 940 words takes about 2 minutes to read. Team Liu Liang, Professor of Forensic Medicine, Tongji Medical College, Huazhong University of Science and Technology, proofread by Wang Yu, has obtained pathological samples of 9 patients who died of the new coronavirus pneumonia.
此前，刘良对新京报记者称，其中3例遗体的初步解剖报告即将发布。
Earlier, Liu Liang told the Beijing News that three of the remains of the preliminary autopsy report is about to be released.
今日（2月28日），新京报记者获得了团队第一份观察报告《新型冠状病毒肺炎死亡尸体系统解剖大体观察报告》，为1例尸体解剖肉眼观察结果。
Today, Feb. 28, the Beijing News reporter obtained the team's first observation report, "New coronavirus pneumonia dead body system autopsy gross observation report," for a case of autopsy naked eye observation.
上诉报告参与作者为4位华中大学同济医学院法医学系人员、5位湖北崇新司法鉴定中心人员和1位上海公安学院人员。
The appeal report was written by four members of the Faculty of Forensic Medicine of Tongji College of Medicine of Central China University, five members of Zhongxin Forensic Medical Center of Hubei Province and one member of Shanghai Public Security Academy.
开展尸体检验距离死亡时间不超过12小时。
The post-mortem examination was carried out within 12 hours of death.
地点为武汉市某医院手术室，解剖人员进行生物安全三级防护，解剖采用干性解剖法及特殊防护步骤。
Located in an operating room of a hospital in Wuhan city, anatomists carried out biosafety level III protection, anatomy using dry anatomy and special protective steps.
“主要是肉眼可见的一些改变，大体观察报告。
"Mainly visible to the naked eye are some of the changes reported in general observations.
”刘良对新京报记者说。
"Liu Liang told the Beijing News.
报告显示，逝者样本是男性，85岁，2020年1月某日以“多发性脑梗死”入院。
The report showed that the deceased were male, 85 years old, and had been admitted to hospital with "multiple cerebral infarction" on some day in January 2020.
入院时无发热、咳嗽等症状。
There was no fever or cough on admission.
入院10天后出现喉咙发痒及发热。
Throat itching and fever 10 days after admission.
入院后第13天确诊为新型冠状病毒感染患者。
A new coronavirus infection was diagnosed 13 days after admission.
入院后28天死亡，临床死亡原因诊断为“新型冠状病毒肺炎、呼吸衰竭”，死亡前3。
28 days after admission, the clinical cause of death was diagnosed as "new coronavirus pneumonia, respiratory failure", 3 before death.
d，血氧饱和度下降至 70%~80%。
d. Blood oxygen saturation decreased to 70% ~ 80%.
从解剖检查来看，尸体胸腔积液量不多，未见大量胸水产生，提示胸腔病变并非浆液性炎症为主。
Anatomical examination showed that the volume of pleural effusion was not much, and no pleural effusion occurred, suggesting that pleural lesions were not mainly serous inflammation.
右侧肺与胸膜重度粘连，提示可能合并感染性胸膜炎。
Severe adhesions of the right lung to the pleura suggest possible co-infection with infectious pleurisy.
刘良等人的结论是，从尸体检验大体观判断，该例死者肺部损伤明显，炎性病变以左肺为重，复阅患者入院第20天CT片，尸体检验肉眼所见与其相符合，且病变进一步发展，提示病毒主要引起深部气道和肺泡损伤为特征的炎性反应。
Liu Liang et al concluded that, judging from the general view of the cadaver examination, the patient's lung injury was obvious, the inflammatory lesion focused on the left lung, repeated the patient's admission to the 20-day CT scan, the unaided examination of the body and the disease further developed, suggesting that the virus mainly caused deep airway and alveolar injury-induced inflammatory response.
此前，进行尸体穿刺时，刘良等人就发现，新冠病毒与SARS和中东呼吸综合征冠状病毒引起的病理特征非常类似。
Earlier, Liu Liang and others found that the new crown virus and SARS and the Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus caused by the pathological features very similar.
但从此例解剖大体观察，肺部纤维化及实变没有SARS导致的病变严重，而渗出性反应较SARS明显。
However, from the anatomy of this case, pulmonary fibrosis and consolidation did not lead to serious lesions caused by SARS, and exudative reaction was more obvious than SARS.
其可能的原因是，该例患者从确诊到死亡仅15天，病程较短。
The possible reason for this is that the patient has a short course of illness from diagnosis to death of only 15 days.
在报告的最后，刘良等人提示了几点开展新冠肺炎尸体检验工作的经验。
At the end of the report, Liu Liang and others suggested a few points to carry out the new crown pneumonia autopsy experience.
如：解剖地点具备负压环境为佳，需具备单独消杀条件，解剖人员需做到生物安全三级防护；采用干性解剖，保证无血液、组织残余物污染外排或遗留于现场；开颅时可用遮盖物加强防护，避免飞溅；尽量减少现场对器官进行分离和切开等。
For example: anatomy site with a negative pressure environment, need to have a separate sterilization conditions, anatomy staff to do biosafety level 3 protection; use of dry anatomy to ensure no blood, tissue residues pollution or left at the site; use of mulch to enhance protection against splashing; minimize site separation and incision of organs.
